column5: I believe they call that species a Buffalo.
Won't happen Doug...nobody cares...it's  a carp...not a Muskie! LOL
Now that's a biggin ... expect been eating corn.
I know nothing about this photo guys but I thought that some of you would appreciate it. I found it on myfishingpictures.com. Apparently its some kind of record.
Hmm wonder what kinda fight would this thing put up?  Considering the size

It's the world record common carp...Caught somewhere in Germany I believe.  It's a MASSIVE fish!!!  The current world record carp video can be seen here - Scroll down the page to the 11th vid: http://www.anglingtimes.co.uk/nav?page=ang...esource=6038646
That's..........gigantic. Massive. Monstrous.  I can't imagine them getting that huge up here but maybe in Europe or something. Wow!
I'm amazed at the ol' boy's strength.
His face says it all. lol.
You would need clothsline and a winch to pull that thing in. How on earth did he even get it on his lap?
THATS HUGE props to the gentleman holding it, though prolly weighs more than him.
Thats a pig!
What the heck has that fish been eating  WOW!  That would be one heck of a fight.  Joey
OMG...something that big would have pulled ME around the lake...LOL
LOL cmmt! Tell me about it, knowing my size, it would have pulled me around, under, in, that lake.LOL

holy crap   that carp is so big im surprised that it can even swim...thats dang huge....where was that thing caught????  that might be a new record of some kind if i caught that carp i would be checking it out    wow thats just amazing
Some more pics here: http://www.limk.com/english/limk/10406/
Thats nothing, I catch those all the time. Throw them back because they're not big enough for my white bucket.
That Carp had to eat a whole lotta Crap to get that big!
That 38.15kg converts to almost 84lbs. Can you say HERNIA?
Call me crazy but doesn't the head look like a beagle?!? -Brian
How long till some sharp eyed viewer states that his right hand looks funny and that the shadows aren't right?  Just wondering.
I think the look on his face says it all .... in one word (and its already been said here but bears repeating) .... HERNIA !  Now thats the reason you dont use 6" augers
Slowpoke,  It does look like a dogs head with floppy ears even!  I see it too!  Maybe we're both nuts lol  Tony
Thanks for the compliment fishergirl72'.  ......and that guys fish is pretty big too.
